ðŸ©º Breast Cancer Detection App

A Streamlit-based web application that predicts whether a breast tumor is Malignant or Benign using a trained TensorFlow Keras model.
The app allows users to input feature values using sliders or paste an array of feature values, and then displays the prediction.

Features

Binary Classification Model (Malignant vs Benign)

Built using:

TensorFlow/Keras for the model

Streamlit for the web interface

Two input options:

Sliders for manual feature entry

Text box to paste an array (e.g., [7.76, 24.54, 47.92, 181.0, 0.0526, ...])

Real-time prediction with one click

Supports auto-loading example samples from the dataset (optional feature)

Tech Stack

Python 3.x

TensorFlow / Keras

Streamlit

Scikit-learn

Numpy, Pandas

Project Structure
